        <h2>Registry</h2>
        <p>After much deliberation, we have decided not to register with any stores. Realistically, because we will both be going back to school in the fall, what we need more than anything else is money to pay for tuition. I know the idea of giving money is not very exciting or romantic, but Daniel and I are both boring and practical people, who love the idea of having needs met before wants (perhaps and I am just a little bit more boring and practical). So if you fall in the group of people who are comfortable giving money, that is much appreciated. However, if you find that you have just turned purple in the face by the utter and complete rudeness of what we just asked, and are now contemplating whether you will even be coming to the wedding at all, first, please, take three deep breaths. Second, know that we would rather have you at the wedding and happy than not at all, so don’t worry about money or gifts and just bring your wonderful self! And remember, keep breathing! If however, you find yourself in a third group, where you are not exactly purple and horrified, but feel disappointed in not being able to give gifts (which I understand is a very important love language), then we have created a registry of sorts online. It is basically a collection of a bunch of things that we think we will want/need. We aren't very picky about the specifics, so we would love it if you could find the best deal! Awesome finds on Kijiji and in thrift stores are also much appreciated.</p>
